<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--McCallumDeath     11-22 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--McCallum Death,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lethal Drug Mixture Killed Jill Ireland's Adopted Son</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 27-year-old adopted son of actress Jill
Ireland died from an accidental mixture of lethal drugs, the
coroner has ruled.
   The type and quantity of drugs won't be disclosed for another
week, but Jason McCallum had a history of abusing heroin, cocaine,
morphine and alcohol.
   ``He died of acute multiple drug intoxication, administered by
ingestion and injection,'' Bob Dambacher of the Los Angeles County
Medical Examiner-Coroner's office said Tuesday. ``It is listed as
accidental.''
   McCallum was found dead Nov. 7. After his burial, Miss Ireland
said she thought her son had shaken his drug habit.
   She adopted Jason while she was married to actor David McCallum,
known for his role as agent Illya Kuryakin in the 1960s television
series ``The Man From U.N.C.L.E.''
   Miss Ireland and David McCallum were divorced in 1967, and she
married actor Charles Bronson a year later. Jason was one of seven
children Bronson and Miss Ireland raised.
   Miss Ireland, 54, is fighting cancer.
