<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0482</SECOND>
<HEAD>Storms Bring Snow, High Winds from Northeast to Plains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Cold winds howled over the Northeast and Plains today, dropping
temperatures into the teens and 20s from Maine to the Dakotas.
   The weather across much of the nation was expected to be colder
than normal through the weekend, with the chill air pushing into
Texas, the Gulf Coast and Florida.
   Light snow was forecast today for Chicago, Denver and
Washington, D.C., and fog was to shroud San Francisco on one of the
busiest travel days of the year. Snow today fell over Minnesota,
where up to 6 inches were possible. Snow ended across Maine by
Tuesday night, but hurricane-force winds were reported near the
coast. Gale warnings extended from Maine to the Virginia coast.
   On Monday, northern New England received up to 13 inches of snow.
   Light rain on Tuesday was scattered over Arkansas, eastern
Oklahoma, southeastern Kansas, New Mexico and southwest Texas.
   High temperatures remained below freezing from eastern North
Dakota through the upper Mississippi Valley to the upper Great
Lakes today, and across northern New England.
   Eight communities in the southern and central high Plains region
had record high temperatures Tuesday for the date, including
Alamosa, Colo., with 61 degrees; Cheyenne, Wyo., 65; Colorado
Springs, Colo., 73; and San Angelo, Texas, 85.
   The nation's high Tuesday was 88 degrees at Presidio, Texas.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EST today:
   _East: Atlanta 52 partly cloudy; Boston 23 windy; Charleston,
S.C., 51 fair; Chattanooga 45 cloudy; Cincinnati 29 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 27 partly cloudy; Detroit 24 fair; Hatteras 47 fair;
Jacksonville 50 fair; Key West 64 fair; Knoxville 38 cloudy; Macon
45 partly cloudy; Miami 61 fair; New York 26 fair; Philadelphia 25
fair; Pittsburgh 22 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine, 19 windy;
Richmond 31 fair; Tampa 58 fair; Washington, D.C., 29 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 17 snow; Chicago 27 cloudy; Denver 38 partly
cloudy; Des Moines 32 cloudy; Indianapolis 30 partly cloudy; Kansas
City 31 cloudy; Little Rock 52 cloudy; Nashville 40 rain; New
Orleans 65 foggy; North Platte 38 partly cloudy; Oklahoma City 56
cloudy; Omaha 29 fair; Rapid City 27 windy; St. Louis 38 cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 23 snow; Sault St. Marie 18 snow; San Antonio
64 rain.
   _West: Anchorage 24 snow; Boise 31 fair; Casper 25 partly
cloudy; Fairbanks 10 snow; Great Falls 21 partly cloudy; Honolulu
76 fair; Las Vegas 52 fair; Los Angeles 60 partly cloudy; Medford
32 fair; Pendleton 37 fair; Phoenix 60 fair; Portland, Ore., 42
partly cloudy; Reno 34 fair; Salt Lake City 32 foggy; San Diego 62
cloudy; San Francisco 50 fair; Seattle 42 fair; Spokane 26 fair.
   _International: Montreal 12 fair; Ottawa 16 fair; Regina 10
foggy; Toronto 10 fair; Winnipeg 1 fair; Mexico City 55 fair;
Acapulco 79 fair.
