<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--JudgeNixon     11-22 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Judge Nixon,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former Federal Judge Disbarred</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Mississippi Supreme Court today
disbarred former U.S. District Judge Walter L. Nixon Jr., who was
removed from the bench by the U.S. Senate earlier this month.
   Nixon, 61, was released Tuesday from a halfway house in New
Orleans, where he was completing a prison term for perjury. He was
convicted in 1986 and sentenced to five years for lying about
discussing a marijuana case with a prosecutor.
   On Nov. 3, the Senate voted overwhelmingly to remove Nixon from
the bench in Mississippi, stripping him of his $89,500 salary. He
had earlier been impeached by the House.
   Under state Supreme Court rules, a felony conviction results in
automatic disbarment.
</TEXT>
