<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--JetRat     11-22 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Jet Rat,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jumbo Jet Grounded After Rat on Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British Airways grounded a Miami-bound jumbo jet
Wednesday after a flight attendant spotted a rat on board.
   The Boeing 747, which had flown to London from Washington, was
being prepared for departure from Heathrow Airport when the flight
attendant saw the rodent scurrying around the passenger cabin, the
airline said.
   None of the 297 passengers had boarded, it said.
   Airline officials said that fumigating the plane would have
taken up to eight hours, so Flight 293 was changed to another jumbo
jet, which left two hours late.
   The rat was caught and the plane fumigated, said an airline
spokeswoman.
   It was not known where the rat got on the plane.
</TEXT>
