<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Students     11-22 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Students,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>China Announces Code For Students</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chinese university students must ``adhere to
socialist collectivism and love labor,'' according to a new code
from the State Education Commission.
   The code will help students ``grow up to be socialist successors
more rapidly,'' said Education Commission official Zhang Renxian.
   The official Xinhua News Agency, which carried the remarks by
Zhang, did not provide details of the code, but said it demands
that students ``defend the interests of the motherland, abide by
the constitution, adhere to socialist collectivism and love labor.''
   It also takes up moral behavior, maintaining public order and
``abiding by the discipline of foreign affairs.''
   The government says that inadequate attention to mental and
physical discipline and political education led to the spring
pro-democracy student movement that was ended by a bloody military
crackdown on what authorities say was a counterrevolutionary
rebellion.
   Since June, all university students have been required to attend
classes on party doctrine and ideology.
   There also has been a renewed stress on physical labor, an
educational practice largely abandoned in the past decade.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
