<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Earle     11-22 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Earle,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Australian Producer Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kevin Earle, who was responsible for
producing the touring shows for many hit musicals in Australia,
died Wednesday of a heart attack. He was 51.
   Touring shows he produced or promoted included ``Evita,''
``Barnum,'' ``Oklahoma,'' ``The Sound of Music,'' ``Oliver'' and
``Cats.''
   Between 1977 and 1984, he was executive manager of the Adelaide
Festival, which became an internationally renowned showcase.
   He left the Festival Trust in 1984 to produce the Australian
touring version of the musical ``Cats.''
   His most recent productions were ``Starlight Express'' in 1987
and the spectacular ``Sound Cloud'' in 1988 _ Japan's official
bicentennial gift to Australia.
   Survivors include his wife, Nancy, a son and two daughters.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
