Street,'' said the rumpled Detective Columbo ``needs a new coat.''
   ``But he's a fabulous character,'' she said. ``When you see him,
you think he couldn't possibly solve anything or be shrewd or
smart. But he's the smartest and shrewdest and the most
calculating.''
