<HEAD>Margaret Chase Smith Remains Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Sen. Margaret Chase Smith planned
to spend Thanksgiving in Maine Medical Center, where she was
recuperating from ``a slight heart problem,'' a hospital
spokeswoman said Wednesday.
   The spokeswoman, Terry McGarvey, said Mrs. Smith, 91, was
expected to return to her home in Skowhegan in a few days.
   Mrs. Smith had requested that no additional information be
released, Ms. McGarvey said.
   Mrs. Smith was discharged Tuesday from Resurrection Hospital in
Chicago after a six-day stay and was flown to Portland, where she
was admitted to Maine Medical.
   She had been admitted to the Chicago hospital Nov. 16, after
suffering a digestion problem on a flight from Bangor to Chicago,
according to friend Merton Henry, a Portland lawyer.
   Henry said Wednesday he was told that the heart problem was
minor. ``It was probably brought on by the big attack of
indigestion she had,'' he said.
