<TEXT>
   The four-day Thanksgiving weekend began with some
tricky driving conditions over much of the Eastern half of the
nation.
   The National Weather Service said Wednesday evening that
snowstorms were scattered over the Southeast, mid-Atlantic states,
the Appalachians, the Ohio Valley and sections of the Great Lakes
states.
