<SECOND>AM-Bush-Louisiana,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>President Declares Three Parishes a Disaster Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Wednesday declared a state
of disaster in three Louisiana parishes hard hit by heavy rains and
flooding earlier this month.
   The disaster declaration covering residents of Jefferson,
Orleans and St. Charles parishes is the fourth federal disaster aid
proclamation in Louisiana this year.
   Bush's proclamation opens the way for Federal Emergency
Management Agency assistance in the way of loans, temporary
housing, grants and other programs to help individuals, businesses
and local governments recover.
   The heavy rains hit Louisiana on Nov. 7-9.
</TEXT>
