<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Hart     11-22 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Hart,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Canadian Filmmaker Hart Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Canadian filmmaker Harvey Hart, who directed
episodes of ``Columbo'' and such television miniseries as ``East of
Eden'' and who was a pioneer director with CBC-TV, died of a heart
attack on Tuesday, aged 61.
   Hart won a Golden Globe Award for ``East of Eden,'' an
adaptation of the John Steinbeck novel.
   His Canadian movies included ``Fortune and Men's Eyes'' and his
U.S. work included the pilots for the series ``Judd for the
Defense'' and ``The Young Lawyers.''
   Producer Victor Solnicki, who developed several projects with
Hart, said the Toronto-born filmmaker ``was proudest of his work
during the golden years of CBC-TV drama. He was one of the first 12
to open the doors at CBC (in 1952) when nobody knew what they were
doing.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
