<HEAD>For Release Friday AMs, Nov. 24, and thereafter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roman Catholic bishops should be careful about
criticizing Catholic politicians, and Catholic public officials
have a moral responsibility to act to limit abortions, according to
guidelines on the abortion debate offered in a religious
publication.
   In an article in a recent issue of America magazine, the Rev.
Robert J. McManus, vicar for education of the Diocese of
Providence, R.I., said Catholic bishops need to make clear they
