<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japan will contribute $150 million to an economic
and political stabilization fund for Poland, whose goal is to raise
$1 billion from Western nations, Kyodo News Service reported
Wednesday.
   Quoting unidentified government sources, Kyodo said Japan would
pledge the contribution at a meeting of aid donors in Brussels on
Friday.
