<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed higher Wednesday, boosted by
moderate gains in early Wall Street dealings.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished 7.2
points, or 0.3 percent, higher at 2,192.3, but down from an early
peak of 2,197.4. At its lowest, the index dipped to 2,186.6 at late
morning.
   Volume was a light 324.2 million shares, down from Tuesday's
modest 350.6 million shares.
   Dealers said a flurry of corporate news ahead of official
dealings helped London to early gains, but that there was a lack of
aggressive follow-through buying.
   The market's upward potential was capped by continuing weakness
in sterling, dealers said. There were fears that Thursday's release
of British trade figures for October could depress the currency and
the London equity market, they said.
